# ybala-admin-app — Project Context

`ybala-admin-app` is the Expo / React Native app for Yabala **staff**. It reimplements
the `admin` and `manager` panels from the web frontend (`yabala-fe`) as a mobile app,
while looking and feeling exactly like the customer app (`ybala-customer-app`).

## Reference projects (siblings of this repo)

| Project | Path | Use it for |
|---------|------|-----------|
| `ybala-customer-app` | `/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/ybala-customer-app` | Design, patterns, typography, components, stack — the app must feel identical to this |
| `yabala-fe` | `/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/yabala-fe` | What pages exist, what each page needs, and who (admin vs manager) can access what |
| `yabala-be` | `/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/yabala-be` | API contracts — routes, request/response shapes, permissions |

## Prime directive

When unsure, consult the source of truth instead of guessing:

- Design / UX / component / styling question -> read `ybala-customer-app`
- Feature / page / permission question -> read `yabala-fe`
- API / endpoint / payload question -> read `yabala-be`

Always match existing conventions rather than inventing new ones.
